Description:
(Free Bag+Spare String+Triangular Plectrum & Local Warehouse 2 Days Delivery) ABOUT UKULELE
Ukuleles are a string instrument made from a hollow soundboard and four strings. They look like a mini guitar. They have an hourglass base and a fingerboard neck. Often, ukulele manufacturers make the strings from stainless steel or nylon, and the instrument's tuning should be (in order) the notes of G, C, E and A.

Feature
This Ukulele is a soprano version that has a basswood body and nylon strings. 
1,Hricane makes High quality constructed Ukuleles. It's not top of the line mind you but it's a good solid instrument perfect for starting out and beyond. 
2,Hricane Ukulele include a Gray neck fingerboard with sturdy 15 brass frets . 
3,This set comes with a high quality gig bag, the gig bag with a shoulder strap that can be taken on and off.
4,The Ukulele is remarkably lightweight. This in combination with the nylon strings makes this instrument a good choice for children who are learning. 
5,Hricane ukulele has the highest pitch of all of the ukuleles,it has a clear and joyful sound 

ATTENTION
The strings need to be tightened when it arrives. You do this by turning the 4 white knobs towards you. Turning them away from you loosens the strings. Their sound quality increases with time as they age. What it sounds like when it first arrives isn't exactly what it will sound like a few weeks or months down the road,with time the sound becomes richer.
